block content
	section.intro-section.building-section: .container
		.section-header
			h2 Get a head-start on the features you need
			p.lead Keystone is the easiest way to build a web application or content-managed website in Node.js
		.row
			.col-sm-6.col-md-4.col-lg-3
				.feature-panel
					h4
						span.feature-icon.entypo.entypo-leaf
						span.feature-label Express.js and Mongo
					p Keystone will configure express - the de facto web server for node.js - for you and connect to your mongo database using mongoose, the leading ODM package.
			.col-sm-6.col-md-4.col-lg-3
				.feature-panel
					h4
						span.feature-icon.entypo.entypo-shuffle
						span.feature-label Dynamic Routes
					p Keystone starts with best practices for setting up your MV* application, and makes it easy to manage your templates, views and routes.
			.col-sm-6.col-md-4.col-lg-3
				.feature-panel
					h4
						span.feature-icon.entypo.entypo-picture
						span.feature-label Database Fields
					p IDs, Strings, Booleans, Dates and Numbers are the building blocks of your database. Keystone builds on these with useful, real-world field types like name, email, password, address, image and relationship fields (and more)
			.col-sm-6.col-md-4.col-lg-3
				.feature-panel
					h4
						span.feature-icon.entypo.entypo-light-bulb
						span.feature-label Auto-generated Admin UI
					p Whether you use it while you're building out your application, or in production as a database content management system, Keystone's Admin UI will save you time and make managing your data easy.
			.col-sm-6.col-md-4.col-lg-3
				.feature-panel
					h4
						span.feature-icon.entypo.entypo-pencil
						span.feature-label Simpler Code
					p Sometimes, async code can get complicated to do simple things. Keystone helps keep simple things - like loading data before displaying it in a view - simple.
			.col-sm-6.col-md-4.col-lg-3
				.feature-panel
					h4
						span.feature-icon.entypo.entypo-docs
						span.feature-label Form Processing
					p Want to validate a form, upload an image, and update your database with a single line? Keystone can do that, based on the data models you've already defined.
			.col-sm-6.col-md-4.col-lg-3
				.feature-panel
					h4
						span.feature-icon.entypo.entypo-users
						span.feature-label Session Management
					p Keystone comes ready out of the box with session management and authentication features, including automatic encryption for password fields.
			.col-sm-6.col-md-4.col-lg-3
				.feature-panel
					h4
						span.feature-icon.entypo.entypo-paper-plane
						span.feature-label Email Sending
					p Keystone makes it easy to set up, preview and send template-based emails for your application. It also integrates with Mandrill (Mailchimp's excellent transaction email sending service)
			.col-sm-6.col-md-4.col-lg-3.hidden-sm.hidden-lg
				.feature-panel
					h4
						span.feature-icon.entypo.entypo-publish
						span.feature-label Managed Updates
					p Keystone includes an optional updates framework, that can take care of running update scripts for you, making it easy to transition from development to production.
	
	
	section.intro-section.admin-section: .container
		.section-header
			h2 Admin Interface
			p.lead A beautiful, customisable Admin UI based on your models
		.text-center: img(src='/images/admin-interface.jpg').img-responsive
	
	
	section.intro-section.tools-section: .container
		.section-header
			h2.text-center What you build is up to you.
			p.lead There are a lot of frameworks that make decisions for you, and many that take decisions away. Keystone doesn't do that. Use the features that suit you, and replace the ones that don't.
		.row
			.col-sm-3
				h4 Built on Express
				p Keystone can configure Express for you, or you can take over and treat Keystone like any other Express middleware.
				p You can also easily integrate it into an existing Express app.
			.col-sm-3
				h4 Built with Mongoose
				p Mongoose, supported by MongoDB Inc, is the leading ODM for node.js and MongoDB. Keystone exposes mongoose to you when you need it, so anything you 
					| can build with MongoDB, you can build with Keystone.
			.col-sm-3
				h4 Lightweight
				p Keystone is designed to be as light as you want - you can pick and choose the features you want to include.
				p Write your own routes, disable the Admin UI, whatever - it's up to you.
			.col-sm-3
				h4 Extendable
				p One of the greatest things about node.js is the vast number of quality packages available.
				p Keystone is designed to let you use any of them, without losing the benefits it provides.
	
